        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Instructions for surveying.

A</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><persName>Mr E. R. Weightman</persName></p>

<p>you can survey a quarter for <persName>G. W. Cock</persName> on a <placeName>Post oak Bayou
west of Trespalacios</placeName>&#8212;not to cross any <placeName>tide or large creek</placeName>&#8212;be
attentive to that rule</p>

<p><date when="1830-10-14">Octr. 14, 1830</date> <persName>S. F. Austin </persName>  [Rubric]</p>

<p>If any <placeName>creek </placeName>is crossed the tract must be narrower than long,
and the narrowest front must be <placeName>on the creek,</placeName> that is that tract can
neither be run square or oblong up and down the <placeName>creek </placeName>for if it
crosses it will have two fronts one on each side, you must use your
discretion as to crossing the <placeName>creek</placeName>, so as not to spoil another <placeName>tract</placeName></p>

<p><persName>S. F. Austin </persName>   [Rubric]</p>


        </div1>
